# Advanced Game Stats Conventions

## Core constraint: every result is a list of games

All Advanced Stats panels return a ranked `List<MasterGameYear>` (or a wrapper like `LongestTenuredGame`) aggregated per game. Never expose individual user, publisher, or league rows — only aggregate counts/metrics keyed by `MasterGameID`.

## Full-stack layer map

```
SQL query (MySQLMasterGameRepo)
  → IMasterGameRepo interface + FakeMasterGameRepo stub
  → InterLeagueService pass-through
  → GameController [HttpGet] action → ViewModel
  → Vue panel component (components/gameStats/*.vue)
  → Registered in advancedGameStats.vue (sections array + v-else-if + VALID_SECTIONS)
```

See `GetMostDreamsDashedGames` / `mostDreamsDashedPanel.vue` as the canonical full-stack example.

## No DB schema changes in this vertical

New stat panels must use existing tables. Schema migrations belong to other feature work.

## Hydration rule

Use `GetMasterGameYear(id, year)` where the correct year is:
- Released game → year of `ReleaseDate`
- Unreleased game → `currentDate.Year`
- Cancelled game (or "highest available") → `MAX(Year)` from `tbl_caching_mastergameyear`

## ViewModel shape

- Stat needs only game data → return `List<MasterGameYearViewModel>` directly, no new ViewModel needed.
- Stat needs extra fields → create a specific ViewModel in `Web/Models/Responses/` wrapping `MasterGameYearViewModel` plus your properties. Use `LongestTenuredGameViewModel` as the pattern, not as a type to reuse.
